last_episode_to_air.name: Lights Out
last_episode_to_air.overview: With their heads on straight from their perfect summer day, our combined Ducks team heads to the Summer Showcase – with Alex as their coach and Cole in a new role, so that he won’t get in Jace’s way

name: The Mighty Ducks: Game Changers
overview: In present day Minnesota, the Mighty Ducks have evolved from scrappy underdogs to an ultra-competitive, powerhouse youth hockey team. After 12-year-old Evan is unceremoniously cut from the Ducks, he and his mom Alex set out to build their own ragtag team of misfits to challenge the cutthroat, win-at-all-costs culture of competitive youth sports.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Season 2 takes us to an intense hockey camp run by Colin Cole, a charming yet hardcore former NHL player. As our team tries to survive, they’re faced with the question: Can you win summer?

tagline: It may be the off season, but it's on.

episodes.name: Game On
episodes.overview: When 12-year-old Evan is cut from The Ducks, he and his mom try to build a new kind of hockey team.

episodes.name: Dusters
episodes.overview: Evan is skeptical of Alex's unique approach to coaching, as the team gets ready for its first game.

episodes.name: Breakaway
episodes.overview: Alex tries to be a real coach. Evan recruits Sofi, and the team gets unexpected help...from Bombay.

episodes.name: Hockey Moms
episodes.overview: Sofi is practicing with both the Ducks and the Don’t Bothers and forges her mother’s signature so she can play for the team. Gordon tries to motivate Alex while helping her prepare to take on Stephanie, her boss, in the Slap Shot Challenge. Meanwhile, Evan and Nick invite Koob to their sleepover.

episodes.name: Cherry Picker
episodes.overview: Evan's father shows up unexpectedly, complicating things for Evan, Alex, and even Bombay.

episodes.name: Spirit of the Ducks
episodes.overview: With the original Ducks team back, Evan and Bombay consider where their loyalty lies.

episodes.name: Pond Hockey
episodes.overview: The team gets mad at Evan, and Alex doesn't think she's a good coach. Bombay takes them to a new place.

episodes.name: Change on the Fly
episodes.overview: With the State Tournament on the horizon, Alex realizes she likes winning more than she thought.

episodes.name: Head Games
episodes.overview: Don't Bothers road trip to States! Teen drama unfolds, Alex is left behind, Bombay reveals a secret.

episodes.name: State of Play
episodes.overview: The Don't Bothers are forced to choose what's really important, as they face the Ducks at States.

episodes.name: Ice Breaker
episodes.overview: Our Mighty Ducks, along with their coach Alex Morrow, head to an elite summer hockey institute in California, run by charming yet hardcore former NHL player Colin Cole. But when Coach Cole tells our squad they may not be a good “fit” for his program, they get fired up to prove him wrong – even though a mysterious camper warns them not to stay.

episodes.name: Out of Bounds
episodes.overview: Training kicks into high gear at EPIC, where cutting edge technology meets physical drills and mental conditioning to push campers to the brink.

episodes.name: Coach Classic
episodes.overview: It’s the annual Coach Classic, where the coaches take the ice against the kids. It’s real smash-mouth hockey, and everyone’s got an agenda.

episodes.name: Draft Day
episodes.overview: It’s Draft Day, when coaches select their teams for tournament play. Alex has thrown down a gauntlet to Coach Cole, and pressure’s on for her to find players who will deliver. Even her own son would rather be drafted to Cole’s elite team.

episodes.name: Icing on the Cake
episodes.overview: Alex leads our crew of old and new Mighty Ducks through their first week of team training with the spirit of summer fun – but she struggles to bring a disengaged Jace into the fold. Coach Cole, meanwhile, drives Team Dominate through power practices, and Evan pushes himself harder than ever.

episodes.name: Twigs
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ducks face rough tournament play where they wonder if team spirit and heart are enough for them to win. Jace struggles with his glitch and resists becoming part of the group. Over on top-notch Dominate, Evan proves himself to be a grinder, and Coach Cole takes notice.

episodes.name: Spirit of the Ducks Part 2
episodes.overview: Alex takes the Ducks on an unsanctioned field trip, hoping some legendary hockey magic will turn the team around. Meanwhile, Evan feels the price of the sacrifices he’s made at EPIC, and he’s determined to become Dominate’s captain to make it all worth it.

episodes.name: Trade Rumors
episodes.overview: Fresh off their visit to the Anaheim Pond, our Ducks have found their “sideways” skills – offbeat ways to succeed on the ice – putting them on a collision course with Coach Cole’s juggernaut Team Dominate.

episodes.name: Summer Breezers
episodes.overview: The Ducks and their rival Dominate get ready to face each other in the Finals – with the champion moving on to the Summer Showcase.

episodes.name: Lights Out
episodes.overview: With their heads on straight from their perfect summer day, our combined Ducks team heads to the Summer Showcase – with Alex as their coach and Cole in a new role, so that he won’t get in Jace’s way
